From: JXR2UltraHDR
Subject: Fix color gamut sRGB - force SDR intent to BT.709 instead of Display P3

libultrahdr's internal tone mapping was setting sdr_intent->cg = UHDR_CG_DISPLAY_P3,
which caused the SDR base JPEG to use Display P3 gamut. Standard JPEG decoders
interpret this as sRGB, resulting in oversaturated colors.

This patch forces the SDR intent to BT.709 (≈ sRGB gamut), which matches what
standard JPEG decoders expect.

diff --git a/lib/src/jpegr.cpp b/lib/src/jpegr.cpp
index 0000000..0000000 100644
--- a/lib/src/jpegr.cpp
+++ b/lib/src/jpegr.cpp
@@ -1983,7 +1983,7 @@ uhdr_error_info_t JpegR::toneMap(uhdr_raw_image_t* hdr_intent,
     return status;
   }

-  sdr_intent->cg = UHDR_CG_DISPLAY_P3;
+  sdr_intent->cg = UHDR_CG_BT_709;
   sdr_intent->ct = UHDR_CT_SRGB;
   sdr_intent->range = UHDR_CR_FULL_RANGE;
 
   ColorTransformFn hdrGamutConversionFn = getGamutConversionFn(sdr_intent->cg, hdr_intent->cg);
